Author: Readmore
Content: This was the basis for my social news site Klipboardz (http://www.klipboardz.com). I built this feature 2 years ago, unfortunately PR is what makes one startup more successful than another, it's not really about features.

Author: Xichekolas
Content:
The advantage they pointed out in the article was energy savings and time in the elevator. Very large buildings have express elevators that won't stop on every floor, or the poor sap on floor 52 would never get there. This is like making every elevator an express one by batching up the stops.

As for the energy savings... not really clear on that. Maybe I just misunderstood.

Author: supahfly_remix
Content:
Wow what a conclusion, companies cluster. It's not as if this hasn't been happening since at least the Industrial Revolution. Also, they picked some of the lamest companies to put in the map: e.g., Fujitsu data systems, National Semiconductor. I think the article was just a placement for Palo Alto Networking.

I expect better of the Times.
